        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 12:14AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1214 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Trent, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Abilene, Anson, Merkel, Tye, Hawley, Trent, Noodle,
Dyess Afb, Hodges, Funston, Truby, and Stith.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 258 and 282.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
